.TH "pdc_rx_buf_pool_create" 9 "pdc_rx_buf_pool_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pdc_rx_buf_pool_create \- Pool of receive buffers used to catch the metadata header returned with each response message.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pdc_rx_buf_pool_create
.BI "(struct pdc_state *pdcs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdcs" 12
PDC state structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The metadata is not returned to the mailbox client. So the PDC driver
manages these buffers.
.SH "RETURN"
PDC_SUCCESS
-ENOMEM if pool creation fails
